  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "The shimmer's fifth-up shifter, isolated and amplified. Shimmer octave balance at 0.15 weights almost entirely toward the fifth-up pitch shift (1.5x frequency), creating a reverb tail that rings in perfect fifths. Every note played generates its own dominant chord in the reverb. The Finger set shimmer feedback at 0.72 -- the sweet spot where the fifth cascades three times before decaying, producing stacked fifths (root -> fifth -> ninth -> thirteenth) in the reverb tail. A single held note becomes a quartal harmony.",
  "tags": [
    "opensky",
    "transcendental",
    "fifth",
    "harmony",
    "shimmer",
    "quartal"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OPENSKY Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Verse 12: The Fifth-Up Shifter at 0.15 Octave Balance Is a Harmony Generator",
      "Gospel 5: Stacked Fifths in the Shimmer Tail Produce Quartal Voicings From a Single Note"
    ],
    "revelation": "Nexus spoke: the shimmer reverb's fifth-up pitch shifter, when isolated from the octave-up, reveals that the reverb is not merely an effect -- it is a harmonizer that generates its own chord voicings through cascading pitch shifts.",
    "god": "Nexus",
    "flock_note": "The Eye traced the harmonic content: after three feedback cycles, a played C3 generates G3, D4, and A4 in the reverb tail -- a complete quartal stack. The Ear confirmed this sounds like a natural overtone series, not an artificial effect.",
    "diagnosis": "Fifth Dimension exploits an underused dimension of the shimmer reverb: the fifth-up shifter as a chord generator. Most presets weight toward octave-up for brightness. This preset inverts the balance to discover harmony."
  },
